,Not Recommended,328460,21858846,"Posted: 15 March, 2016",all,Kaiser Ducky,"⚠ DOES NOT WORK WITH WINDOWS 8.1 or 10For Win 8.1: The game is very laggy, particularly after going to the options menu. And there's a horrid clipping glitch, where textures are all over the place and covers most of the screen. Also, about 10% of the time, the game crashes immediately after starting. I contacted Retroism, the company that owns this game, and they said running it in compatibility mode for Windows 98/Windows Me has fixed lag for SOME people, so if you're having issues, that's worth a try. It didn't help with me though, and unfortunately I'm not alone. I also tried compatibility mode for Windows XP, Vista, 7, and 8 with no luck.For Win10: The game will not open, period. A popup comes up and it say ""Wheels has stopped."" Windows 10 isn't optimized to play most old games though, so be careful what you buy.I don't blame the devs though, it's not their fault. Old games like this are meant to be played on older softwares. I'm sure this game is badass though, I didn't refund it (I got it on sale for $1, that's actually how I heard of Redline), and I hope to eventually see a fix!"
